---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Souls Quick Menu"
  description="A Skyrim mod that brings a Dark Souls–style radial quick menu to the game — with 115k+ downloads on Nexus Mods."
>
  <article class="document">
    <p class="label" data-animate>
      <a href="/fun" class="back">← Fun stuff</a>
    </p>
    <h1 data-animate>Souls Quick Menu</h1>
    <p class="muted stat-line" data-animate>Skyrim mod · 115k+ downloads on Nexus Mods</p>
    <hr class="rule" data-animate />

    <p data-animate>
      Souls Quick Menu is a mod for The Elder Scrolls V: Skyrim that brings a
      <em>Dark Souls</em>–style radial quick menu into the game. Instead of
      pausing to dig through the favorites menu, you assign your weapons,
      spells, shouts, and items to a quick-access wheel and cycle through them
      on the fly — keeping you in the moment when a fight gets hectic.
    </p>
    <p data-animate>
      It started as a small personal itch — combat in Skyrim always felt like it
      paused for inventory management — and grew into something the wider
      community adopted. To date it's been downloaded more than 115,000 times,
      which is easily the most-used thing I've ever shipped to strangers on the
      internet.
    </p>

    <p data-animate>
      <a href="https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/72238" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
        View Souls Quick Menu on Nexus Mods ↗</a
      >
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .back {
    border-bottom: none;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
  }
  .back:hover {
    color: var(--accent);
  }
  .stat-line {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--fs-sm);
    margin-top: var(--space-1);
  }
</style>
